      "content": "those neutral ones are better for a standard news app. but i was thinking about how different outlets cover these things. like, if this was a group of people protesting for something like \"tax reform\" or \"environmental laws,\" would the headlines still be \"intense\" or \"chaotic\" initially? or do you feel like the nature of the protest (like racial justice stuff) makes it more likely to be framed as \"chaos\" or \"riots\" by default? just trying to understand the tone differences.",
