      "content": "I think the nature of the protest does influence the tone of the headline. Protests for issues like tax reform or environmental laws tend to be more subdued and focused on the specific cause. In contrast, protests for racial justice or social issues often carry a sense of urgency and emotional intensity, which can lead to headlines that emphasize the chaos or unrest. This is because these types of protests often involve long-standing social injustices, and the media may feel pressure to convey the gravity and passion of the issue. As a result, headlines like \"chaos\" or \"riots\" might be more commonly used to describe these types of protests, even if they're not necessarily the most accurate description.",
